reviews.text: This item was bought because the lighting store I took my vintage floor lamp to didn't want to install a dimmer (as I requested) into the new wiring. Instead, they went online - printed out the page for this product and told me to order it instead of them doing the job they agreed to do. The quality seems ok - I'm not sure how the sliding dimmer switch will hold up long term. The lamp is something I don't use everyday but is set up in a reading nook in my office. Time will tell about it's longevity and durability. It seems a bit plasticy - but everything seems that way now a day. At the end of the day - it does dim the lamp (which is what I purchased it to do). I'll update this review in the future once I've had a chance to use it more.

reviews.text: First, I can't believe I never knew these type of dimmers existed. I can now say that I don't think I could do without them! I have two of these for our bedroom lamps on our nightstands and they are so convenient. My husband goes to bed early and I dim my lamp to where I can see when I come into the bedroom. But it's dim enough that it doesn't disturb his sleep. I bought another brand for a lamp in the family room, but believe me, the dimmer switch on this lamp slides a lot smoother.
